description: I thought it strange that this one has two heads. Upon closer inspection, the stems were joined from base up. They didn't separate until the flower.
In weedy area, near ranger station, Underhill State Park

tag_list: dandelion, danelion, red seeded dandelion, weeds
description: We have a grip of these growing in the adjacent lot next to the apartment.  I remember eating them as a kid when I visited my Nana. I don't find myself collecting them now, but often old Chinese ladies will roll through and pick the yard clean of these tasty weeds.
Seems odd to see a dandelion in what should be the dead of winter.
